      "strengths_deep_dive": [
        "Al-Mawrid US excels in financial stability and administrative leaneness. According to its <cite id=\"10\">2023 Form 990</cite>, the organization managed to keep its <cite id=\"11\">program expense ratio at 75.2%</cite>, which is a commendable level of direct service funding for an educational entity. Furthermore, its governance structure is characterized by a <cite id=\"12\">100% independent board</cite>, ensuring that oversight remains free from internal conflicts of interest. This structural integrity is paired with a clear <cite id=\"13\">Zakat-eligible status</cite>, allowing Muslim donors to fulfill their religious obligations through programs that serve the <cite id=\"14\">fisabilillah, fuqara, and masakin</cite> categories."
      ],
      "summary": "Al-Mawrid United States Inc, also known as the Ghamidi Center of Islamic Learning, is a non-profit organization dedicated to promoting a rational and objective understanding of Islam. Founded in <cite id=\"1\">2014</cite>, the organization serves as a primary vehicle for the religious research and educational methodology of Javed Ahmad Ghamidi. The charity reported <cite id=\"2\">$816,038 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 tax year, primarily driven by <cite id=\"3\">$704,499 in public contributions</cite>. Its operations focus on making Islamic scholarship accessible through modern media, including the <cite id=\"4\">AskGhamidi platform, live weekend programs, and the '23 Questions' video series</cite>. While the organization maintains a global reach through digital translation initiatives, its financial footprint remains concentrated, with <cite id=\"5\">75.2% of expenses staying within the United States</cite>. The charity holds an <cite id=\"6\">overall score of 84.84.5/100 from Charity Navigator</cite>, reflecting a solid foundation in accountability and culture, though it faces challenges in scaling its direct impact relative to its operating costs.",
